{
  "stem": "3605.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Lohamei ha-Geta'ot.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is the Fighters' Museum.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they-- they-- some of the pamphlets were delivered there by some of the underground people that managed to survive from our group, and not many.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I am sorry to say that a very great percentage of the people that were fortunate to join the underground perished, too.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know whether 5% survived from the underground fighters.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And talking about the underground fighters, the contact person that came to us, not just brought us the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] underground newspaper, but we also knew what was happening around.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in 1941, the end of it, and in the beginning of 1942, there were already happening the mass murders in Chelmno.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] collecting the Jews in buses in the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so, anyhow, the situation started being very, very grave.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there was no tomorrow.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Germans weren't anymore the cultural people like they were looked upon through our eyes and the eyes of all European people.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They let themselves be led, blind, by their Fuhrer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they had a blind allegiance.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And in 1941, on the Wannsee Conference, they decided to liquidate all the Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they were hoping that there will be nobody to tell about their story of crime and inhumanity.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember one evening I dared-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] across the street, I-- where we lived, I had my very closest girlfriend.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I thought, it is just such a short way, I'm going to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] take my chances.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, when you are young you take chances.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I ran over.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I succeeded to run over.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we were walking in the courtyard by my girlfriend, and a German saw us.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
